# MCP server allowlist — turns on .claude/hooks/mcp-gate.sh enforcement.
#
# Copy this file to .claude/mcp-allowlist.txt and list, one per line, the MCP
# server names you trust. Any MCP tool call (mcp__<server>__<tool>) whose
# <server> is NOT listed here is BLOCKED by the gate hook.
#
# The server name is what you configured in .mcp.json / settings — e.g. a server
# registered as "linear" exposes tools like mcp__linear__create_issue, so list
# "linear" below. Run /mcp-audit to see configured servers and which are missing.
#
# Without a .claude/mcp-allowlist.txt (this .example doesn't count), the gate is
# inert: it never blocks, it only reminds you once per session that MCP output is
# untrusted input. Create the real file to enforce.
#
# Lines starting with # and blank lines are ignored.

# linear
# github
# sentry
